        <section>
            <h2>The Concept</h2>
            <p>Traditional streaming is fragmented and slow. By combining Stremio (the interface) with Real-Debrid (the high-speed source), you create a private, centralized library that outperforms any standard subscription service.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Requirements</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Stremio:</strong> The open-source media player.</li>
                <li><strong>Real-Debrid Account:</strong> A premium service for high-speed cached links.</li>
                <li><strong>Torrentio:</strong> The essential add-on bridge.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Setup Steps</h2>
            <p><strong>1. Real-Debrid:</strong> Sign up for an account and locate your API Key in the user settings. This is your personal access token.</p>
            <p><strong>2. Configure Torrentio:</strong> Visit the Torrentio configuration page. Select "Real-Debrid" as your provider and paste your API Key.</p>
            <p><strong>3. Final Sync:</strong> Click install to link the configuration to your Stremio app. Your library will now sync across your Android phone, PC, and TV.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="important-box">
            "By using Debrid servers, your ISP only sees an encrypted connection to the service, keeping your viewing habits private and your speeds unrestricted."
        </div>

